(790, 'LEAD', 'Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) is an important cause of morbidity and mortality worldwide and has a tremendous impact on the individual patient, the healthcare system, and the general public. Contrary to other chronic diseases, the natural history of COPD, commonly described as the natural decline of lung function, has not been investigated sufficiently. Understanding normal lung development and ageing, both in health and disease, and in men and women, is considered a research priority in current respiratory medicine and is essential to properly interpret results of eventual therapeutic interventions. , Therefore, we intend to asses a) the age-related natural decline in lung functions in the general population, b) the prevalence of COPD and the development of major respiratory symptoms in this disease, c) the prevalence of the most important COPD comorbidities (eg. cardiovascular, metabolic and cognitive dysfunction) and d) the association between the natural decline of lung function and socioeconomic status, individual long term exposure to air pollution and other toxic inhalants and comorbidities. , To our knowledge this health examination survey will be the first investigation in Austria providing information about the most prevalent respiratory disease worldwide, its comorbidities and underlying causal factors in a longitudinal approach.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:AT_MUW:collection:BB9067', 'collection', 3, 1),
