(829, 'Vienna Bleeding Study (molecularbiological)', 'Blood coagulation disorders are diseases of the hemostatic system, which have a common symptom of bleeding tendency. The plasmatic coagulation disorders hemophilia A and B as well as the Willebrand syndrome are the most common and therefore the most studied changes. They occur both as a congenital as well as acquired disease. In addition, there are other congenital or acquired disorders that require treatment. These include thrombocytic and hyperfibrinolytic coagulation disorders as well as decreased concentration or activity of various other plasmatic coagulation factors., The aim of the present study is to evaluate the influence of molecular biological changes and their functional effects in congenital blood clotting disorders.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:AT_MUW:collection:BB9188', 'collection', 3, 1),
