(930, 'Establishment of a blood sample bank in the field of gynecological oncology', 'The ability to use blood samples from cancer patients represents a major advantage for clinically related basic research at a university hospital. Theoretical institutes and companies in most cases lack this possibility. Therefore, a bank is to be established for future research projects in the field of gynecological oncology, in which blood samples are to be continuously introduced. These samples should be available for later investigations (e.g., for the analysis of prognostic or predictive tumor markers, genetic analyzes (polymorphisms, LOH in tumors)). Furthermore, the detection of disseminated tumor cells in these samples should be conducted.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:AT_MUW:collection:BB9432','collection', 3, 1),
