(1012, 'CRC Brussel Diabetes Biobank', 'The Diabetes Biobank Brussels (DBB) is associated with the Belgian Diabetes Registry, a nationwide clinical network of more than 200 diabetologists and researchers from more than 100 clinical centers, comprising the vast majority of universitary and conventioned departments of endocrinology and pediatrics in Belgium. Since 1989, the network has collected more than 100,000 questionnaires with standardized clinical information and blood samples from: > 10,000 recent-onset diabetes patients aged 0-39 years at diagnosis (all types, predominantly type 1 diabetes in that age category) > 10,000 of their first-degree relatives aged 0-39 years', 'bbmri-eric:ID:BE_71014391000:collection:001','collection', 5, 1),
(1013, 'Tumorbank UZ Brussel', 'The Tumorbank UZ Brussel is part of The Belgian Virtual Tumourbank, a Belgian consortium of 11 hospitals, among which all major Belgian university hospitals. We collect tumor samples and associated human tissues (normal tissue, blood, urine,...) in several collection methods (frozen, paraffin,...).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:BE_71014391000:collection:002','collection', 5, 1),
