(1041, 'BBCVA', 'This Biobank is a research biobank created to better understand the physiopathology of arterial diseases e.g. atherosclerosis, fistulas and aneurysms.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_BBCVA','collection', 23, 1),
(1042, 'Biobanque du Centre des Thérapies Expérimentales (CTE-BBO)', 'The CTE-BBO was created with the following scientific goal(s): to support care and research missions, and to preserve patient samples for possible immunotherapy treatment (under the seal of a specific study consent)', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_CTE','collection', 23, 1),
(1043, 'Biobanque CURML Sudden cardiac death', 'In this biobank are stored samples from SCD cases. Sudden cardiac death (SCD) is a major public health problem. The underlying cause of SCD is most frequently coronary atherosclerotic disease in elderly victims, while genetically determined cardiomyopathies, such as hypertrophic, arrhythmogenic, or canalopathies prevail in young people. In case of potential genetic origin of cardiac pathologies, pathologists are then involved in a multidisciplinary investigation on surviving family members. The role of the pathologist is to perform an autopsy, to diagnose the case, to keep post-mortem samples according to legal and ethical guidelines and upon negotiation, to orient relatives of SCD’s victims to a genetic counselling.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_CURMLSuddencardiacdeath','collection', 23, 1),
(1044, 'OptiSurg', 'Nutrition et chirurgie vasculaire', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_OptiSurg','collection', 23, 1),
(1045, 'Research biobank on the indesirable effects of psychotropic drugs', 'The biobank is constituted of blood, urine and stool samples, clinical and genetic data from donors involved in research projects on the adverse effects of psychotropic drugs.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_PSYCHOTROPIC','collection', 23, 1),
(1046, 'BB-URS', 'The BB-URS aims to collect biological samples and genetic data of psychiatric patients and healthy controls that are recruited in research projects conducted by the URS team or in collaboration with national and international partners.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_URS','collection', 23, 1),
(1047, 'Urology Biobank', 'The Urology Biobank is dedicated to the collection of samples from urological cancer patients for the research projects of the Urology Research Unit and scientific collaborations.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_Urology','collection', 23, 1),
(1048, 'Dermatology Biobank', 'The scope of the Dermatology Biobank is to conduct research in the field of dermatology and venereology. It includes especially skin tissue and PBMC from patients and study volunteers from the Dermatology DataSource of CHUV.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_CHUV:collection:CH_dermatochuv','collection', 23, 1),
(1049, 'Microbiome_IEM', 'Sampling of biological material to characterise microbiota in children with inborn errors of metabolism', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_ETH:collection:CH_Microbiome_IEM','collection', 24, 1),
(1050, 'Microbiome_NEC', 'Sampling of biological material to characterise the change in microbiota over time in children with risk of necrotzising enterocolitis and late-onset sepsis and their healthy family members.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_ETH:collection:CH_Microbiome_NEC','collection', 24, 1),
(1051, 'Covid-19 Ticino Biobank', 'This COVID-19 Ticino Biobank was established to a unified Swiss web-based cohort for prospective high-quality baseline and follow-up data registration of COVID-19 patients hospitalized, according to standardized directives. This Biobank will provide a platform for carrying out scientific research projects on COVID-19 and allows collaborations with reference networks to elucidate clinical presentation, natural history, response to treatment, immune response and cytokines activation, and outcomes of the disease.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_FondazioneEpatocentroTicino:collection:Covid-19TicinoBiobank','collection', 25, 1),
(1052, 'Swiss Autoimmune Liver Disease', 'The aim of the present registry with its biobank is to collect high quality prospective data and biosamples on rare diseases in order to elucidate epidemiology, natural history, response to treatment and outcome. In addition, the biobank allows addressing specific scientific issues on a variety of open questions. The registry will provide a platform for carrying out scientific research projects on AILD. In addition, the registry will allow collaborations with reference networks on AIH, PBS and PSC abroad.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_FondazioneEpatocentroTicino:collection:SwissAutoImmuneLiverDisease','collection', 25, 1),
(1053, 'SCREEN-RA:  a Swiss cohort study of first-degree relatives of rheumatoid arthritis patients', 'The SCREEN-RA biobank: Blood samples were routinely collected from healthy first-degree relatives of patients with RA (RA-FDR), known to have an increased risk of developing RA as compared to the general population .Since 2010, over 1500 FDR-RA across Switzerland have enrolled. Blood samples are routinely sampled for serum, genomic DNA and total RNA collection. In a subset, stool samples and oral examinations are also performed for microbiota assessment.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_HUG:collection:CH_Screen-RA','collection', 26, 1),
(1054, 'AneuX - Intracranial Aneurysm Domes Biobank', 'Human intracranial aneurysm domes obtained during microsurgery by resection of the aneurysm dome after clipping of the neck. All samples are collected at the Neurosurgery division of the Geneva University Hospitals.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_HopitauxUniversitairesGeneve:collection:CH_AneuX','collection', 26, 1),
(1055, 'BaHOP', 'BaHOP houses a disease-focused biobank. It is a liquid, human, public owned biobank established to promote research to improve prevention, diagnosis, and therapy in the field of oncology, hematology, and immunology on pediatrics diseases.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_HopitauxUniversitairesGeneve:collection:CH_BaHOP','collection', 26, 1),
(1056, 'Geneva Brain Bank', 'The  Geneva Brain Bank collects tissues since 1926. It contains today more than 10''000 formalin-fixed human autopsy brains with clinical documentation, neuropathological diagnoses, the corresponding paraffin-embedded tissue blocks (often from whole brains slices), several thousand histological slides and several hundred frozen tissue blocks.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_HopitauxUniversitairesGeneve:collection:CH_GenevaBrainBank','collection', 26, 1),
(1057, 'Familial Hypercholesterolemia biobank (FH)', 'The FH biobank contains DNA from index case with a clinical phenotype of familial hypercholesterolemia (Dutch Lipid Clinic Network score of 6 or more), as well as their relatives. After extraction from EDTA blood tube, DNA is stored at -80°C.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_ICH:collection:CH_FH','collection', 27, 1),
(1058, 'PINIT', 'We are collecting samples from sick and healthy children from the area Immunology, Infectiology and Stem Cell Transplantation. We collect left overs and extra material.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_KinderspitalZurich:collection:CH_PINIT','collection', 28, 1),
(1059, 'Swiss Pediatric Haematology and Oncology Biobank Network', 'The SPHO Biobank Network stores samples received from Centers of the Swiss Paediatric Oncology Group (SPOG), in collaboration with Tissue Banks of Swiss Pathology Institutes. Donors to the Biobank are patients suffering from oncological diseases, benign hematologic diseases, undergoing hematopoietic stem cell transplantation for any indications or individuals related to pediatric diseases (for example, family members of donors).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_KinderspitalZurich:collection:CH_SwissPediatricHaematologyOncologyBiobankNetwork','collection', 28, 1),
(1060, 'Liquid Biobank Bern', 'The Liquid Biobank Bern (LBB) consists of an institutional collection of patients from the Inselspital, Bern University Hospital. Blood samples (Plasma, Serum, DNA) of patients of the Inselspital including the clinical patient data are collected and stored for the future use of research projects.  A high sample quality suitable for omics analysis is achieved by fast track (~1h from needle to freeze), an highly automated and standardized processing, and storage in fully automated robotic stores (at -80°C and N2) by the state-of-the-art infrastructure of the Inselspital, operated by the Center for Laboratory Medicine. The samples are tightly tracked by their barcodes and each time-point (from blood draw to storage) is set by robots/scanners to grant a high data quality.    The samples are collected specifically for this biobank (no leftover material) to achieve this controlled, standardized fast track processing. This hospital cohort was initiated by the Inselspital to facilitate biomedical research by supplying samples of high quality. The goal is to improve prediction, prevention, diagnosis and therapy in human medicine. With the collected samples and data, underlying mechanisms of diseases can be researched.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_LBBservices:collection:CH_LiquidBiobankBern','collection', 29, 1),
(1061, 'SHeS-Bern Pilot Phase Biobank', 'The SHeS-Bern Pilot Phase biobank is part of the human biomonitoring pilot project (Swiss Health Study Pilot phase: SHeS Pilot phase). This population-based cohort has been launched by the Federal Office of Public Health (FOPH) in Switzerland to prepare the implementation of a future national program. The aim is to identify health and exposure indicators, which are central to the understanding and monitoring of health and disease in the general population. The biobank includes biological material together with a large amount of data (health examinations, questionnaires).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_LBBservices:collection:CH_SHeSBernPilotPHaseBiobank','collection', 29, 1),
(1062, 'SHeS-Vaud Pilot Phase Biobank', 'The SHeS-Unisanté Pilot Phase biobank is part of the human biomonitoring pilot project (Swiss Health Study Pilot phase: SHeS Pilot phase). This population-based cohort has been launched by the Federal Office of Public Health (FOPH) in Switzerland to prepare the implementation of a future national program. The aim is to identify health and exposure indicators, which are central to the understanding and monitoring of health and disease in the general population. The biobank includes biological material together with a large amount of data (health examinations, questionnaires).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_LBBservices:collection:CH_SHeSUnisantePilotPHaseBiobankVaud','collection', 29, 1),
(1063, 'Biobanque Génomique du CHUV', 'Réservoir d''échantillons biologiques et de données cliniques des patients du CHUV, la BGC est une ressource de premier ordre pour la médecine génomique. La BGC est une biobanque hospitalière Suisse créée par le CHUV et l''UNIL en 2013. L''objectif de cette biobanque est de contribuer à la découverte de nouvelles thérapies et de mesures préventives en offrant aux chercheurs un accès sécuritaire et dépersonnalisé aux données et échantillons de qualité. Une prise de sang pour la BGC peut être réalisée chez tout patient du CHUV qui signe le consentement général. Le plasma isolé du sang total et l’ADN extrait des cellules sont mis à disposition des chercheurs pour de futures analyses.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_LPA:collection:CH_BiobanqueGenomiqueDuCHUV','collection', 30, 1),
(1064, 'Bioledger', 'Patient-specific organoids starting with gastro-intestinal organoids of healthy and Cystic Fibrosis patients.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_SunBioscience:collection:CH_Biole','collection', 31, 1),
(1065, 'Swiss Spinal Cord Injury Cohort Study', 'The SwiSCI biobank will provide a platform for testing scientific and medical hypothesis and work in a synergy with the Swiss Spinal Cord Injury Cohort Study (SwiSCI). As an epidemiological study, SwiSCI will provide major assets for biobanking: a nation-wide and representative study population; prospective lifetime follow up of participants; potential for genetic and metabolic association studies comparing SCI to the general population; and a data model facilitating international collaborative research.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_SwissParaplegicResearch:collection:CH_SwiSCI','collection', 32, 1),
(1066, 'PFZ-UKBB - Biobank', 'This biobank governs the use and the access to samples collected as left-over material from clinical routine and left-over of reserach projects.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_UKBB:collection:CH_UKBB','collection', 33, 1),
(1067, 'Biobank Pathology at USB', 'The Pathology Department at the USB operates a biobank called "Biobank Pathology UniSpital Basel" (hereinafter BPUSB) for an indefinite period in conjunction with the clinics of the USB. Samples (tissues and bodily fluids) and patients'' information are included in the biobank for use in the context of diagnosis / treatment as well as in ongoing and future diagnostic quality assurance that has yet to be determined. The BPUSB also keeps biological material for current and future test developments and research projects. The biobank has been financed until now by the Pathology Department of the USB and will continue to be for the time being.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_UniversitatsspitalBasel:collection:CH_BPUSB','collection', 34, 1),
(1068, 'Swiss Transplant Cohort Study Biobank', 'A multicenter biobanking system to harvest, store and deliver DNA, plasma and live PBMC samples taken just before, at 6 months and 12 months after solid organ and hematopoietic stem cell transplant, for research related to transplantation. Centers: Universitätsspital Basel (USB), Universitätsspital Insel Bern, Hôpitaux Universitaire de Genève (HUG), Centre Hospitalier Universitaire Vaudois (CHUV), Kantonsspital St. Gallen, Universitätsspital Zürich (USZ). Www.stcs.ch.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_UniversitatsspitalBasel:collection:CH_STCSB','collection', 34, 1),
(1069, 'Biobank of the Swiss HIV Cohort Study', 'The biobank of the Swiss HIV Cohort Study contains viable blood mononuclear cells (once per calendar year per patient), plasma samples (at least once per calendar year per patients) and purified DNA for the majority of patients.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_USZ:collection:CH_SHCS','collection', 35, 1),
(1070, 'Tissue Biobank USZ', 'As integrative part of the Department of Pathology and Molecular Pathology, University Hospital Zurich, the Tissue Biobank USZ manages formalin-fixed, frozen and live cell samples and information from patients of the USZ and other hospitals according to the guidelines of the Human Research Act (HFG) and international guidelines.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_USZ:collection:CH_TissueBiobankUSZ','collection', 35, 1),
(1071, 'FABER cohort', 'Describe the reproductive health of young Swiss men in relation to geographic variation and evaluate the association between semen quality and environmental/ lifestyle factors to which men were exposed to in-utero and during adulthood.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_Unige:collection:CH_FABER','collection', 36, 1),
(1072, 'Tissue Biobank Bern', 'The Tissue Bank Bern manages samples and information from patients of the Inselspital and other hospitals in the catchment area of the Institute of Pathology, University of Bern, according to the guidelines of the Human Research Act (HFG) and international guidelines.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_UniversityOfBern:collection:CH_TissueBiobankBern','collection', 37, 1),
(1073, 'VetSuisse Biobank, VET_GEN_BERN', 'The VET_GEN_BERN collection of the Vetsuisse Biobank stores EDTA blood and genomic DNA samples from domestic animals (cats, dogs, goats, sheep, cattle, horses).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:CH_UniversityOfBern:collection:CH_VetSuisseBiobankVETGENBERN','collection', 37, 1),
