(1224, 'Resource with Liquid Biospecimens and Image Data', 'All liquid biospecimens with associated clinical data and image data come from DZHK-funded studies that are obtained using standardized procedures at all study centers via the DZHK''s research platform. As a result, our resource is growing steadily.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_DZHK:collection:DCZHK','collection', 65, 1),
(1225, 'DZHKomics Resource', 'This control resource was generated from around 1,200 healthy people. It serves as a basis of comparison for the more precise determination of differences between healthy and sick people - not only for cardiovascular research. Approximately 1,150 whole genome sequences consist of SNVs, Indels and approx. 48 million variants. In addition, there are RNA sequence data from around 700 test persons. Corresponding basic phenotypes are also available.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_DZHK:collection:DOZHK','collection', 65, 1),
(1226, 'Biomaterials of transplanted patiens of the DZIF Transplant Cohort', 'Biomaterials from patients, who received a transplantation of heart, liver, kidney, pancras or stemcells:  - EDTA Buffy Coat - EDTA Plasma - EDTA Serum - Isolated PBMCs - Stabilized RNA  - Stool - Urine', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_KDEB:collection:DZIF-TxCohort','collection', 66, 1),
(1227, 'EHEC-HUS', 'At Medical Clinic I, serum and blood from all EHEC/HUS patients at the clinic were prospectively collected during the EHEC outbreak in Germany in early summer 2011. The samples were collected at diagnosis and then every three months thereafter. EHEC: Enterohaemorrhagic Escherichia coli. HUS: hemolytic-uremic syndrome.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_EHEC:collection:EHEC-HUS','collection', 67, 1),
(1228, 'Main Collection of CCCF Freiburg', '', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_FREEZE-CCCF:collection:CCCF','collection', 68, 1),
(1229, 'Main Collection of FREEZE Freiburg', '', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_FREEZE-CCCF:collection:FREEZE','collection', 68, 1),
(1230, 'Fever without source', 'The Bernhard Nocht Institute for Tropical Medicine collects samples of various materials from febrile, inpatially and healthy children aged 0-15 years in Ghana. Clinical and partly socio-economic data are collected additionally. Throat swabs and blood were taken from healthy children. Depending on the symptom complex, the following samples were taken from the sick children: blood, urine, stool, cerebrospinal fluid, throat swab. All samples undergo extensive diagnostics.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_FWSBNITM:collection:FWS','collection', 69, 1),
(1231, 'Main collection of GCKD-Biobank, comprising of all the samples.', 'The German Chronic Kidney Disease (GCKD) study represents a prospective observational national cohort study of patients with CKD in Germany. The main specific aims of the study are (i) to identify and validate risk factors and markers associated with the progression of CKD and the development of end stage renal disease (ESRD), (ii) to identify and validate risk factors and markers associated with cardiovascular disease (CVD) events and CVD progression in the setting of CKD. Central storage of high quality biomaterials is a central component of the study concept to allow establishing associations between biomarkers, patient characteristics and outcomes. The GCKD Study has established a network that combines a central coordinating center in Erlangen with nine regional centers at collaborating academic institutions (Aachen, Berlin, Erlangen, Freiburg, Hannover, Heidelberg, Jena, München and Würzburg). The GCKD-Study is governed by a Steering Committee which is formed by representatives of the coordinating center, each regional center and cooperating institutes. Six members from the Steering Committee have been elected to the Executive Publication Committee to review proposed publications according to the publication policy and to an Ancillary Studies Committee to channel and harmonize ancillary study proposals according to the ancillary studies policy. The GCKD Steering committee must take all decisions about biomaterial utilization. Members of the study consortium can negotiation biomaterials; application forms and processes for evaluation are in place. Biomaterials have already been shared with sites in Germany, Switzerland and the US', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_GCKD:collection:all_samples','collection', 70, 1),
(1232, 'Collection Airway coloniztion ad CF Hannover', 'Pseudomonas aeruginosa (PsA) is a hallmark pathogen of the lung disease in cystic fibrosis (CF) patients. Chronic PsA colonization is a central factor in the course of CF lung disease. PsA contributes considerably to morbidity and mortality, and also has a significant impact on quality of life and the costs of CF treatment.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:AC_ad_CF','collection', 71, 1),
(1233, 'Collection AGO Paola Hannover', '"Patients with advanced FIGO IIIB-IV high quality serous or endometrioid ovarian, tubal or p Ri males peritoneal carcinoma treated with the standard - First-line therapy in combination with a pla Tin- taxan-bevacizumab-containing chemotherapy and Bevaci - To be considered as maintenance therapy  "', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:AGO_Paola','collection', 71, 1),
(1234, 'Collection CF-Register Hannover', 'Improved results in paediatric liver transplantation have gradually shifted focus of clinical research from increasing patient survival to enhancement of long-term quality of life. One of the major challenges today is to optimise immunosuppression post transplantation in order to reduce drug toxicity and infection, whilst maintaining adequate immunosuppression to prevent rejection and graft loss. One of the difficulties in achieving this goal lies in understanding the functional level of therapeutic immunosuppression.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:CF_Register','collection', 71, 1),
(1235, 'Collection Digit HF Hannover', 'DIGIT HF is a study for the therapy of cardiac insufficiency, which is funded by the german Federal Ministry of Education and Research (BMBF). The aim is to examine whether the active substance digoxin, which increases the contraction force of the heart, can prolong the life of patients with a certain form of cardiac insufficiency and reduce their hospital stays. Digitoxin belongs to the group of digitalis preparations that can be used - originally from the thimble - for selected patients for the treatment of cardiac insufficiency or cardiac arrhythmia.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:DigtHF','collection', 71, 1),
(1236, 'Collection HBV-Cure Hannover', 'Chronic hepatitis B virus infection has not yet been cured. A control of viral replication with inhibitors of the reverse transcriptase (nucleoside analogues) is possible in over 90%. However, nucleoside analogues have only a very small influence on the cccDNA, the HBV template in the cell nucleus of the liver cell. Therefore, the main goal of the overarching DZIF project is to find new concepts to achieve the goal of "HBV Cure".', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HBV_Cure','collection', 71, 1),
(1237, 'Collection Human Genetics Hannover', 'Samples of patients from the routine of human genetics counseling.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HG','collection', 71, 1),
(1238, 'Collection Human Genetics-Chromosome Instability Hannover', 'Our goal is to elucidate mechanisms of chromosomal instability in MDS and in hematological stem cells. We are investigating the connections of the origin of CIN more closely.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HG_CI','collection', 71, 1),
(1239, 'Collection Human Genetics-Tumor Hannover', 'Samples from patients from the routine of human genetics Tumour counselling.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HG_T','collection', 71, 1),
(1240, 'Collection HIB MH01 Psychiatrie Tourette', 'The Project is part of the MHH-HIB collection. Patient collective: inclusion criteria: - Patients with chronic primary tic disorders (chronic motor tic disorder, chronic vocal tic disorder, Tourette Syndrome) - secondary tic disorder - temporary tic disorder', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH01_Psychiatrie_Tourette','collection', 71, 1),
(1241, 'Collection HIB MH02 Pneumologie Asthma', 'The Project is part of the MHH-HIB collection.  Patient collective: Patients with severe bronchial asthma of various origins (allergic or intrinsic).  Inclusion criteria:  -  Eosinophilia (>300 Eosniophile / ml blood)  - Therapeutic option Administration of anti IL-5 antibody (exhausted conventional therapy (LABA, LAMA, high dosis of  ICS +/- oral steroid therapy)).  Longitudinal sampeling will be conducted before and during the anti IL-5 antibody therapy respectively.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH02_Pneumologie_Asthma','collection', 71, 1),
(1242, 'Collection HIB MH03 Kardiologie Kardiomyopathie', 'The project is part of the MHH-HIB collection. The blood samples will be obtained in context of a comprehensive cardiomyopathy registry, which is currently being established at the MHH. Patients will be observed over several years and repeated collection of blood samples during the follow up is planed.   Patient collective:  Inclusion criteria:  - Dilated cardiomyopathy  - noncompaction cardiomyopathy  - inflammatory cardiomyopathy  - metabolic cardiomyopathy  - secondary cardiomyopathy (toxic infiltrative storage diseases)  - restrictive cardiomyopathy   Exclusion criteria:  - Ischemic heart disease as an underlying disease  - Heart valve diseases as an underlying disease  - Congenital heart defects  - Primary pulmonary arterial Hypertension  - hypertensive cardiac disease', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH03_Kardiologie_Kardiomyopathie','collection', 71, 1),
(1243, 'Collection HIB MH05 Nuklearmedizin Prostatakarzinom', 'The Projekt is part of the MHH-HIB collection. Patient collective: Patients with advanced, castration-refractory prostate cancer who will undergo a new molecular-directed radionuclide therapy(PSMA-ligand-therapy)targeting the prostate-specific membrane Antigen. Patients will be treated every 8 weeks and extensive laboratory chemistry, imaging and clinical characterization will be carried out every 8 - 16 weeks. Blood samples will be colected before the first therapy and at 3 timepoints after a Treatment cycle.  Inclusion criteria: - Patients with advanced, castration-refractory prostate cancer with progress under guideline-compliant androgen blockade and progress under chemotherapy -Extensive characterization using a standardized panel of laboratory Parameters (blood count, extensive clinical chemistry, PSA, testosterone) - Extensive characterization of whole-body tumor burden and its heterogeneity by means of molecular Imaging (PET/CT) - Characterization of renal function using laboratory parameters and kidney scintigraphy (clearance)  exclusion criteria: - Lack of PSMA expression of the metastases (PET/CT) - restricted bone marrow reserve - Higher grade kidney failure - ECOG > 2 - Life expectancy < 3 month', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH05_Nuklearmedizin_Prostatakarzinom','collection', 71, 1),
(1244, 'Collection HIB MH06 Gastroenterologie Autoimmunhepatitis', 'This Project is part of the HIB collection. Samples from patients with autoimmun hepatitis. The projekt is also part of the KFO250', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH06_Gastroenterologie_Autoimmunhepatitis','collection', 71, 1),
(1245, 'Collection HIB MH07 Kardiologie Herzinsuffizienz', 'The Project is part of the MHH-HIB collection Patient collective: Patients with symptomatic heart failure who are included in the use case cardiolog in the HIGHmed project. For all patients a defined dataset will be collected. The data will be analyzed by medical informatics techniques to identify patients with high risk for hospitalization caused by worsening of heart failure. After identification of These patients, the patients will be intensively monitored to prevent future hospitalization. The biosamples will be collected to perform advanced scientific studies to identify new disease mechanisms', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH07_Kardiologie_Herzinsuffizienz','collection', 71, 1),
(1246, 'Collection HIB MH08 Kardiologie Endokarditis', 'The Project is part of the MHH-HIB collection. The applicant plans to establish a endocarditis register in cooperation with the Klinik for nuclear medicine and other cliniks of the MHH. Nearly all patients with suspected endocarditis will be examined by echocardiography. Therefore, patients for the endocarditis Register can easily be identified. The Register will comprise structured data records of all patients including klinical data, laboratory data and multimodal Imaging (echocardiography, leukocyte scintigraphy, PET/CT, Imaging of inflamation with tracer-antibodies', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH08_Kardiologie_Endokarditis','collection', 71, 1),
(1247, 'Collection HIB MH10 Strahlentherapie', 'The Project is part of the MHH-HIB collection. Patient collective: Patients with early side effects during radiotherapy of a Tumor disease (at beginning of the irradiation series, low dose irradiation) Inclusion criteria: -Definitive radiotherapy of a Tumor disease  - Age ≥ 18, consent ability - complete medical anmanesis with medication - early radiogenic side effects Exclusion criteria: - palliative radiotherapy (not curative) - monogenic hereditary diseases - planed radiation dose not achieved', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH10_Strahlentherapie','collection', 71, 1),
(1248, 'Collection HIB MH11 Nephrologie', 'Samples from the polyclinic of nephrology for hypertension patients.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:HIB_MH11_Nephrologie','collection', 71, 1),
(1249, 'Collection Hautgewebebank Hannover', 'Establishment of a skin tissue collection for severely burned patients.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:Hautgewebebank','collection', 71, 1),
(1250, 'Collection of the apheresis of dialysis patients Hannover', 'Plasma collection of the apheresis of dialysis patients.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:IMU_Ne_Aph','collection', 71, 1),
(1251, 'Collection KFO311 TP1 Hannover', 'The TP1 examines in a common register prospectively all patients who are treated with a support system due to an acute or terminal failure of the heart or lung; This is the extra extracorporeal Membranoxigenierung (ECMO, Veno-Arterial, Venovenös), Transvasal introduced in the left or right ventricle Microaxialpumpen (e.g. Impella) and also the surgically implanted ventricular assist-devices (VAD).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:KFO311_TP1','collection', 71, 1),
(1252, 'Collection Neocyst Hannover', 'Network for Early Onset Cystic Kidney Disease: NEOCYST is a multicenter, interdisciplinary network of clinicians and scientists exploring early onset cystic kidney diseases. Hereditary cystic kidney diseases are among the most important causes of chronic renal failure in childhood. The goals of NEOCYSTare to increase the knowledge on the epidemiology, the phenotypical spectrum, the underlying genetic and pathophysiological mechanisms as well as the individual prognosis of early onset cystic kidney diseases and thereby to improve the clinical management and counselling of affected patients.  NEOCYST ist ein multidisziplinäres, multizentrisches Netzwerk zur Erforschung zystischer Nierenerkrankungen des Kindesalters. Es handelt sich um einen Verbund aus Klinikern, Genetikern und Wissenschaftlern, die gemeinsam das Ziel verfolgen, die Betreuung, die Therapie sowie die Lebensqualität von Patienten mit zystischen Nierenerkrankungen zu verbessern. Erbliche zystische Nierenerkrankungen repräsentieren eine der häufigsten Ursachen eines chronischen Nierenversagens im Kindesalter. Gleichzeitig zählen sie zur Gruppe der „Seltenen Erkrankungen“, so dass nur wenige hundert Patienten in Deutschland betroffen sind. Alle zystischen Nierenerkrankungen zeichnen sich durch ein hohes Maß an phänotypischer wie genetischer Variabilität aus. Zudem erschweren erhebliche Krankheitsüberschneidungen eine frühzeitige Diagnose sowie eine individuelle Beratung betroffener Patienten und deren Familien.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:Neocyst','collection', 71, 1),
(1253, 'Collection Porto-Pulmonary Hypertension-MHHHannover', 'Porto-pulmonary hypertension is a pre-capillary pulmonary hypertension associated with hepatic disease or portal hypertension.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:PPH-MHH','collection', 71, 1),
(1254, 'Collection Probase Hannover', 'A modern concept for general PSA screening is being investigated in the PROBASE study (risk-adjusted prostate cancer early detection study based on a "baseline" PSA value in young men - a prospective multicenter randomized trial). In this risk-adapted strategy, the PSA tests are performed as a function of the individual risk of the man, which is determined by means of a basic PSA value at the age of 45 or 50 years.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:ProBase','collection', 71, 1),
(1255, 'Collection Q-Map Hannover', 'In the Q-Map study (quality markers to access processing delay), the extent to which the delayed processing of blood and urine samples has an influence on later analyzes, in particular whether metabolites can be used as markers for such delayed processing ( Metabolites are metabolic products such as sugars, fats, amino acids, etc.) and whether a delayed isolation of blood cells from blood samples, eg by transport times, has an influence on the yield and viability of these cells. Overall, this study is designed to continuously improve and test the quality of biomaterials.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:Q_MAP','collection', 71, 1),
(1256, 'Collection REBIRTH active woman Hannover', '"REBIRTH aktiv women" is a study of the Hannover Medical School, which involved female employees between 45 and 60 years, provided they had never before done sports. About 300 staff members, from the nursing staff to the laboratory assistant, reportedly practiced 30 minutes a day. The scientists had already suspected that sports are fit. The fact that the effects set such a clear signal, no one had expected: The physical life could be reduced by more than ten years within this short time.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:REBIRTH-AW','collection', 71, 1),
(1257, 'Collection TX-Kohorte Hannover', 'The DZIF Transplant Cohort is unique in Germany and aims to help improve treatment of patients who have already received a donor organ or had a stem cell transplant.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:TX_Kohorte','collection', 71, 1),
(1258, 'Collection Tourette MHHannover', 'Ziel der Studie ist es, die relativ seltene Erkrankung Tourette-Syndrom genauer untersuchen zu können und möglicherweise die Diagnostik oder Behandlung der Patienten zu verbessern. Für zukünftige Forschungsfragen ist eine derartige „Tourette-Biobank“ von großer Bedeutung.  Patientenkollektiv:  Einschlusskriterien sind Patienten mit chronischen primären Tic-Störungen (chronisch motorische Tic-Störung, chronische vokale Tic-Störung und Tourette-Syndroms)  - jedes Alter  - Männer und Frauen  Ausschlusskriterien:  - sekundäre Tic-Störungen  - vorübergehende Tic-Störung', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:TouretteBB','collection', 71, 1),
(1259, 'Collection Chino Hannover', '"The aim of this study is to investigate the change in leukocyte populations in patients treated with checkpoint inhibitors with malignant diseases. For this purpose, lymphocyte receptors and histamine receptors from blood samples are analyzed more precisely in order to get important insights into the therapy with checkpoint inhibitors. "', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:chino','collection', 71, 1),
(1260, 'Collection GAIN Hannover', 'Das German multi-organ Auto-Immunity Network (GAIN) ist ein Zusammenschluss von Ärzten und Wissenschaftlern der Universitäten Freiburg, Hannover, München und Kiel mit dem Ziel der Erforschung von Multi-Organ-Autoimmunerkrankungen. Multi-Organ-Autoimmunerkrankungen gehören zu den sehr seltenen Erkrankungen und werden häufig durch monogenetische Mutation in bestimmten immunregulatorischen Genen ausgelöst.   Das GAIN Projekt soll die Pathophysiologie untersuchen und neue genetische Ursachen identifizieren,. Auch soll ein Patientenregister und eine Biobank für Multi-Organ-Autoimmunerkrankungen aufgebaut werden. Die gesammelten Probe und Daten sollen zukünftig internen und externen wissenschaftlichen Projekten zur Verfügung stehen. Die Untersuchung der gesammelten Patientenproben soll Einblicke in die Funktion und das Zusammenspiel der betroffenen Gene mit dem Immunsystem ermöglichen. Diese sind von besonderem Interesse für die Wissenschaft, da sie sich auch auf häufiger auftretende Erkrankungen des Immunsystems übertragen lassen. Durch das Verständnis der zugrunde liegenden molekularen Pathogenitätsmechanismen soll die Voraussetzung geschaffen werden, das Gleichgewicht des Immunsystems wieder herzustellen und so langfristig die Patientenversorgung zu verbessern. Hierfür wegweisend ist bereits eine begleitende klinische Studie (ABACHAI) für Patienten mit CTLA4-Insuffiziens, die eine personalisierte, also auf ihre Mutation abgestimmt, Therapie erhalten.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:gain','collection', 71, 1),
(1261, 'Collection Lung-Tx Hannover', 'For patients with the most severe end-stage pulmonary disease, such as COPD, the only curative therapy option is lung transplantation, which is reserved for a highly selective patient population. Especially in the case of lung transplantation, an increasing mismatch of potential organ receivers to organ donors is observed, which leads to a progra- tient mortality of the patients on the waiting list.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HUB:collection:lung_Tx','collection', 71, 1),
(1262, 'Collection TX-Kohorte München', 'The DZIF Transplant Cohort is unique in Germany and aims to help improve treatment of patients who have already received a donor organ or had a stem cell transplant.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_HMGU:collection:TX_Kohorte','collection', 72, 1),
(1263, 'KORA: health research in the region of Augsburg', 'KORA is a population based study on participants living in the region of Augsburg, Germany; KORA collects biosamples and data since 1985 and consists of a number of different surveys and follow-up surveys.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_Helmholtz-MuenchenBiobank:collection:DE_KORA','collection', 72, 1),
(1264, 'Biomarkers for Motoneuron and neurodegenerative diseases (BIO-MNDEG)', 'Motoneuron diseases (MND) are rapidly progressive neurodegenerative disorder that presents with the variable deterioration of the corticospinal tract, brainstem, and spinal anterior horn neurons. MND has increasingly come to be recognized as a “syndrome,” with markedly heterogenous progression rates and pathological courses, despite the existence of clinically well-defined phenotypes; the clinical and pathological overlap with frontotemporal dementia has also rendered the “single system, single disorder” hypothesis tenuous. Advances in modern genetics have led to the identification of over 10 genes linked to the familial form of the disease (fMND); however, the vast majority of cases are sporadic (~90%), with as yet poorly understood etiology. Crucially, there exists no disease-modifying treatment or “cure” for MND, nor any definitive diagnostic test. There is, therefore, an intense need to establish biomarkers that assist with diagnoses, prognostic stratification, and disease activity; of particular value would be biomarkers that are sensitive to the substantial variation in progression rates and can consequently be used to inform therapeutic choices. Knowledge of an individual patient''s course at the time of diagnosis would facilitate effective care planning and resource targeting. Given the complexity and heterogeneity of MND, it is unlikely that a single biomarker will be able to accomplish all of the objectives listed above. It is far more plausible that a “multimodal panel” of biomarkers with varying kinetics and specificities for different parts of the disease process will possess clinical utility. Therefore, this repository aims to build a panel of numerous bio-tissues that capture the range of pathogenic processes at play in MND and related neurodegenerative disorders.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:BIO-MNDEG','collection', 73, 1),
(1265, '(1,3)-β-D-glucan Based Diagnosis of Invasive Candida Infection in Sepsis (CANDISEP)', 'Candisep is a German randomized controlled multicenter trial to investigate the effect of an early antifungal therapy guided by (1,3)-β-D-glucan measurement versus standard of care on 28-day mortality in patients with severe sepsis or septic shock and an increased risk for an invasive candida infection. Heparin- and EDTA-plasma is taken after randomization and on the days 1 to 9 after randomization. Samples are processed locally according to standardised operating procedures and stored centrally at -80 °C.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:CANDISEP','collection', 73, 1),
(1266, 'Systems Medicine of Community Acquired Pneumonia (CAPSyS)', 'CAPSyS is a sub-study of the PROGRESS study of the Pneumonia Research Network on Genetic Resistance and Susceptibility for the Evolution of Severe Sepsis. The CAPSyS add-on protocol expands the observational, longitudinal case-cohort study PROGRESS by adding sample collection from the upper and lower airways and assessments addressing barrier function in the lung. The CAPSyS protocol is activated in selected study centers and applied to ventilated patients on ICU. Activation of the CAPSyS protocol can commence up to seven days after hospitalization for CAP. Patient''s progress is followed in much detail for up to six days after protocol activation. Further data are collected until discharge from the hospital. Patients are followed up on at days 28, 180, and 360.  Baseline assessment comprises sociodemographic, anamnestic, family history, and live style information. Pneumonia risk stratification scores Pneumonia Severity Index (PSI) and CURB-65 are determined upon enrolment. At enrollment and for up to six subsequent study days routine laboratory data, clinical observations, and information on therapy are documented. The Sequential Organ Failure Assessment (SOFA) score, Systemic Inflammatory Response Syndrome (SIRS) status, and organ dysfunction are documented for the same time frame. Starting with enrollment, up to six consecutive sets of biomaterials are collected comprising serum, plasma, and materials for extraction of RNA. Blood for extraction of DNA is collected once. Airway materials (nasal and throat swabs, tracheal secretion, bronchoalveolar lavage) are obtained at protocol activation and tracheal secretion again five days after. Follow up comprises vital status, housing situation, recurrence of pneumonia, and a quality of life questionnaire. CAPSyS addresses the airway and lung compartment in patients enrolled into the PROGRESS study. The aim is to better understand the lung microbiome and barrier function in CAP patients in regard to patient heterogeneity regarding outcome in the hospital and the development of novel treatment concepts.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:CAPSYS','collection', 73, 1),
(1267, 'Hydrocortisone for Prevention of Septic Shock (HYPRESS)', 'Severe sepsis is a disease with a high mortality. Development of shock is a most serious complication and increases the risk of death considerably. Application of low dose hydrocortisone is currently recommended only in patients after severe septic shock has been established. Hydrocortisone therapy has a hemodynamic stabilizing effect and may reverse shock, however, the preventive application has not been investigated in a larger study. The study investigates whether low dose hydrocortisone prevents the development of shock in patients with severe sepsis. It is postulated that shock prevention may also affect morbidity and mortality. HYPRESS is a placebo-controlled, randomised, double-blind study to investigate the efficacy and safety of low dose hydrocortisone to prevent the development of septic shock in patients with severe sepsis.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:HYPRESS','collection', 73, 1),
(1268, 'Prospektive diagnostische Studie: Innovative Diagnostik für Pneumonien bei Immunsuppression (IDES)', 'Sample collection of patients with immunosuppression with or without pneumonia Sample collection of age-matched healthy controls', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:IDES','collection', 73, 1),
(1269, 'Conversion of alpha linolenic acid (KoALA)', 'The KoALA study focuses on the impact of variations in the background diet as a confounding factor. The intake of linoleic acid (LA, C18:2 n-6) has been suggested to diminish the metabolism of α-linolenic acid (ALA, C18:3 n-3) to eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA, C20:5 n-3) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA, 22:6 n-3. In this context, NuCo Study III will be conducted to evaluate the influence of the background diet, in particular the impact of the simultaneous intake of LA on the conversion of ALA into their long-chain (LC) metabolites, the incorporation of n-3 LC-PUFA in human tissues and their metabolism into eicosanoids and docosanoids. Further, the influence of a regular intake of milk fat, in particular from free-grazing ruminants, on n-3 PUFA metabolism will be investigated, because short- and middle-chain fatty acids as well as the branched-chain fatty acids in milk fat may influence the conversion of ALA into n-3 LC-PUFA (hypothesis). Thus, validated nutrition concepts for increasing n-3 LC-PUFA status from plant sources will be developed.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:KoALA','collection', 73, 1),
(1270, 'Comparison of Two Antibiotic Regimen (Meropenem Versus Meropenem+Moxifloxacin)in the Treatment of Severe Sepsis and Septic Shock (MAXSEP)', 'Severe sepsis and septic shock are diseases of infectious origin with a high risk of death. Antibiotic therapy is mandatory but it is unknown whether one antibiotic alone is sufficient for initial therapy. The purpose of this study is to compare a therapy with meropenem alone or the combination of meropenem plus moxifloxacin in the treatment of severe sepsis/ septic shock. Patients randomly receive one of the two treatments for at least 7 days but not longer than 14 days. MAXSEP is a prospective, randomized, open, multicentre study about the effect of an empirical antibiotic monotherapy with meropenem (Meronem®) versus a combination therapy with moxifloxacin (Avalox®) on organ dysfunction in patients with severe sepsis and septic shock.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:MAXSEP','collection', 73, 1),
(1271, 'Prospective Observational Study on Hospitalized Community Acquired Pneumonia (PROGRESS)', 'PROGRESS is a study of the Pneumonia Research Network on Genetic Resistance and Susceptibility for the Evolution of Severe Sepsis. In this observational, longitudinal case-cohort study, patients are enrolled within 48 hours of hospitalization and patient''s progress is followed in much detail for up to six days. Further data are collected until discharge from the hospital. Patients are followed up on at days 28, 180, and 360.  Baseline assessment comprises sociodemographic, anamnestic, family history, and live style information. Pneumonia risk stratification scores Pneumonia Severity Index (PSI) and CURB-65 are determined upon enrolment. At enrollment and for up to six subsequent study days routine laboratory data, clinical observations, and information on therapy are documented. The Sequential Organ Failure Assessment (SOFA) score, Systemic Inflammatory Response Syndrome (SIRS) status, and organ dysfunction are documented for the same time frame. Starting with enrollment, up to six consecutive sets of biomaterials are collected comprising serum, plasma, and materials for extraction of RNA. Blood for extraction of DNA is collected once. Follow up comprises vital status, housing situation, recurrence of pneumonia, and a quality of life questionnaire. It is a major aim of PROGRESS to understand and predict patient heterogeneity regarding outcome in the hospital and to develop novel treatment concepts.  The PROGRESS study was retrospectively registered on May 24th, 2016 with ClinicalTrials.gov: NCT02782013.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:PROGRESS','collection', 73, 1),
(1272, 'Placebo Controlled Trial of Sodium Selenite and Procalcitonin Guided Antimicrobial Therapy in Severe Sepsis (SISPCT)', 'Severe sepsis and septic shock are diseases of infectious origin with a high risk of death. The purpose of this study is to determine whether the intravenous application of selenium (given as sodium-selenite) can reduce mortality in patients with severe sepsis or septic shock. Additionally, it is investigated, whether the measurement of procalcitonin - a marker of infection - can be used to guide anti-infectious measures in this disease. SISPCT is a prospective, randomized multicenter trial of adjunctive intravenous therapy with sodium-selenite(Selenase®, double-blinded) and a procalcitonin guided causal therapy (Open) of severe sepsis or septic shock.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:SISPCT','collection', 73, 1),
(1273, 'Therapeutic drug monitoring-based dose optimisation of piperacillin/tazobactam to improve outcome in patients with sepsis (TARGET)', 'Sepsis is a life-threatening organ dysfunction caused by a dysregulated host response to infection with hospital mortality in excess of 40% despite modern supportive care. Along with insufficient and delayed empirical antimicrobial therapy, inappropriate antimicrobial exposure has been identified to negatively affect patient outcomes. Using therapeutic drug monitoring (TDM) guided antimicrobial therapy with dosing tailored to the altered pharmacokinetics of the individual patient in combination with continuous infusion may be an appropriate strategy to overcome the problems of under- and overdosing of beta-lactam antibiotics. This current trial will address the question whether a TDM-based treatment approach in patients with sepsis and continuous infusion of piperacillin/tazobactam will result in a greater resolution of organ dysfunction and hence better clinical outcome compared to dosing according to manufacturers’ recommendations.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:TARGET','collection', 73, 1),
(1274, 'Collection TARGETFN Jena', 'Samples from adult patients with febrile neutropenia treated with Piperacillin-Tazobactam', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:TARGETFN','collection', 73, 1),
(1275, 'Efficacy of Volume Substitution and Insulin Therapy in Severe Sepsis (VISEP)', 'The purpose of this trial is to determine the influence of colloid versus crystalloid volume resuscitation and of intensive vs conventional insulin therapy on morbidity and mortality of patients with severe sepsis and septic shock. VISEP is a prospective randomized multicenter study on the influence of colloid vs crystalloid volume resuscitation and of intensive vs conventional insulin therapy on outcome in patients with severe sepsis and septic shock.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IBBJ:collection:VISEP','collection', 73, 1),
(1276, 'Main Collection ICB-Lübeck', 'ICB-L main collection, comprising all samples', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_ICBL:collection:ICBL','collection', 74, 1),
(1277, 'LD-HRCT - Early detection of lung cancer and mesotheliomas', 'The collective is made up of employees who were exposed to asbestos dust for at least 10 years prior to 1985 and who are or were smokers (at least 30 pack years) or who have a recognized occupational disease BK 4103.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:LDHRCT','collection', 75, 1),
(1278, 'MoMar - Early detection of lung cancer and mesotheliomas', 'A large prospective cohort of subjects exposed to asbestos was recruited in 2008 - 2018 to validate a panel of markers as part of preventive examinations in northern Germany, North Rhine-Westphalia and in the Rhine-Neckar region in high-risk collectives. The markers cover three molecular levels: proteins / peptides, DNA methylation and microRNAs.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:MoMar','collection', 75, 1),
(1279, 'PURE - Early detection of bladder cancer', 'Incident cases with a histologically confirmed tumor of the bladder; (Exclusion criteria: cancer outside the urogenital tract) Control group: Incident cases with another histologically confirmed tumor or inflammatory diseases of the genitourinary tract Control group (healthy): population-based healthy controls via the Residents'' Registration Office (exclusion criterion: all types of cancer)', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:PURE-HB','collection', 75, 1),
(1280, 'PURE - Early detection of lung tumors and mesotheliomas', 'Patients with diseases of the lung or pleural tumors; Patients with benign diseases of the lungs and pleura, as well as with lung and pleural metastases of other primary tumors; Healthy control subjects from population-based controls from the study region (Einwohnermeldeamt)', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:PURE-L','collection', 75, 1),
(1281, 'PURE - verification of biomarker for the early detection of lung cancer and mesothelioma', 'The verification of the marker candidates from PURE Lunge 1 using a general clinical collective.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:PURE-L2','collection', 75, 1),
(1282, 'Shift work - nurses', 'Health effects of shift work. Investigation of the influence of shift work on the metabolome and hormone profiles in nurses.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:Shift-Work','collection', 75, 1),
(1283, 'PURE – Early detection of recurrence of bladder cancer', 'Marker-assisted aftercare of patients with non-muscle-invasive low / intermediate-risk bladder tumors. Sample collection time: 2016 -2020, in hospitals in Erlangen, Tübingen, Herne, Rostock, Nürnberg', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:Urofollow','collection', 75, 1),
(1284, 'UroScreen - Early detection of bladder cancer in chemical workers', 'Molecular epidemiological studies of bladder cancer in chemical workers 2003-2011. A highly stressed collective (ODIN) has been cared for in-depth occupational medicine for 10 years. All cases of bladder cancer that occurred in this group were recorded. The tumor material was submitted to the IPA for molecular biological analysis.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IPA:collection:Uroscreen','collection', 75, 1),
(1285, 'Study of Health in Pomerania', 'The Study of Health in Pomerania (SHIP) is an epidemiological, population-based study in Western Pomerania. Prevalence and incidence of common risk factors, subclinical disorders and clinical diseases have been assessed since 1997 in five-year intervals. The third follow up (SHIP-3) was assessed between 2014 and 2016. In addition, an independent representative population sample was investigated between 2008 - 2012 (SHIP-TREND). Recently, the first follow up of this cohort has been started (SHIP-TREND-1).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_IRB:collection:SHIP','collection', 76, 1),
(1286, 'Plasma-PBMCcoll', 'Blood cell isolates (e.g. buffy coat) from 200 donors (approx. 50 samples are collected annually), plasma samples from 3000 donors (approx. 800 samples are collected annually).  Clinical data exist of the donors and there are study-specific declarations of consent.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_InfektLMU:collection:Plasma-PBMCcoll','collection', 77, 1),
