(1290, 'LIFE-CHILD-Study Leipzig', 'LIFE Child ist eine prospektiv bevölkerungsbezogene Kohortenstudie im Großraum Leipzig zur Erforschung molekularer Ursachen von umwelt- und lebensstilassoziierten Erkrankungen im Kindes- und Jugendalter. Dazu untersuchen und befragen wir bereits Schwangere ab der 24. Schwangerschaftswoche und deren Säuglinge im 3., 6. und 12. Lebensmonat. Kinder ab einem Jahr laden wir jährlich mit ihren Eltern ein, unseren Studientag zu durchlaufen. Durch die Breite der Rekrutierung hat diese Studie sowohl ein Längs- als auch ein Querschnittdesign. Somit bietet sich eine Vielzahl an Möglichkeiten der Auswertung. Das Ziel der Studie ist es, aus den gewonnenen Informationen die multifaktoriellen Ursachen von Zivilisationskrankheiten zu bestimmen, deren Risikofaktoren zu identifizieren, und die jeweiligen Mechanismen zu verstehen, um zukünftig der Entstehung bzw. Ausprägung dieser Krankheiten wirksam vorbeugen zu können.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_LMB:collection:LIFE_CHILD','collection', 78, 1),
(1291, 'LTX', 'DNA, cDNA/RNA, isolated blood cells, fluids and tissue', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_LTX:collection:LTX','collection', 79, 1),
(1292, 'HIV-HCV collection', 'About one third of all HIV patients in Europe are coinfected with hepatitis C (HCV). The presence of HIV-associated immunodeficiency accelerates the course of HCV-mediated liver disease, leading to fibrosis, cirrhosis and hepatocellular carcinoma. Therefore, mortality rates associated with liver disease in this patient population have increased in recent years. The biobank of the Medical Clinic I of the University Hospital Bonn aims to identify genetic and immunological markers that play a role in the immunopathogenesis of both HIV and HCV. A special focus is on liver diseases and the relation to clinical data.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_MedBonn:collection:MedBonn-HIV-HCV','collection', 80, 1),
(1293, 'Lymphatic Filariasis', 'The aim of the studies in the Specht research group at the Institute of Medical Microbiology, Immunology and Parasitology is to test the therapeutic efficiency of antibiotics against lymphatic filariasis and onchocerciasis.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_MikroBonn:collection:Filariasis','collection', 81, 1),
(1294, 'Immunmonitoring', 'The aim of the sample collection is to use the samples as positive controls for immune monitoring in order to verify the quality of the stains / stimulations.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_MIKROTUM:collection:IMMON','collection', 82, 1),
(1295, 'Neuro-Biobank Tübingen', 'collection of blood samples, Serum, Plasma, CSF, PBMC´s, DNA, Fibroblasts, Urine, Stool and RNA from patients with neurological diseases', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_NBT:collection:MainCollection','collection', 83, 1),
(1296, 'Main collection of the National Register for Congenital Heart Defects', 'Blood, Saliva and Cardiac Tissue (incl. derived material: DNA, RNA etc) from Patients with Congenital Heart Defects and Family Members', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_NRCHD:collection:all_samples','collection', 84, 1),
(1297, 'Stiftung PATH Biobank', 'PATH Biobank is a breast cancer biobank in Germany focused on fresh frozen tumor tissue, blood serum samples and corresponding FFPE-tissue', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_PATH:collection:all_samples','collection', 85, 1),
(1298, 'PEPSI', 'We collect blood/plasma samples from HCV-infected patients for HCV resistance testing. We also collect treatment and viral load data from the patients. These data are then used for molecular epidemiology as well as development of HCV therapy-optimisation tools (geno2pheno[HCV]).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_PEPSI:collection:PEPSI','collection', 86, 1),
(1299, 'Popgen Biobank', 'Popgen is a comprehensive biobank and database for population-based and disease-specific questions as well as a central infrastructure for conducting epidemiological studies. Popgen is used to investigate molecular and non-molecular risk factors for numerous civilization diseases (e.g. diseases of the cardiovascular system, inflammatory diseases, neurological diseases or cancer). Through a better understanding of the molecular and non-molecular basis of these diseases, the biobank is intended to contribute to improved prevention, diagnosis and treatment options in the future.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_P2N-Popgen:collection:popgen','collection', 87, 1),
(1300, 'Existing collection of COVID-19 cases', 'Existing collection of COVID-19 cases', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_RWTHCBMB:collection:COVID19','collection', 88, 1),
(1301, 'Ability to collect COVID-19 cases', 'Ability to prospectively collect COVID-19 cases for new research collaborations.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_RWTHCBMB:collection:COVID19PROSPECTIVE','collection', 88, 1),
(1302, 'Collection of RWTH cBMB Broad Consent Aachen', 'Die Schwerpunkte der RWTH cBMB-Forschungsprojekte sind im Bereich onkologischer, kardiologischer und neurologischer Erkrankungen und entsprechen damit der strategischen Ausrichtung der Forschung der Medizinischen Fakultät der RWTH Aachen.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_RWTHCBMB:collection:RWTHCBMB_BC','collection', 88, 1),
(1303, 'TxChirTUM', 'More than 100 organ transplants (liver, kidney and combined pancreas / kidney transplantation) are performed every year at the Surgical Clinic and Polyclinic of the Klinikum rechts der Isar at the Technical University of Munich. The Biobank collects standardized tissue from recipients and donors as part of kidney, pancreas and liver transplants.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_TxChirTUM:collection:TxChirTUM','collection', 89, 1),
(1304, 'Safety and Efficacy of Induced Pluripotent Stem Cell-derived Engineered Human Myocardium as Biological Ventricular Assist Tissue in Terminal Heart Failure', 'The BioVAT-HF trial will test the hypothesis that cardiomyocyte implantation via engineered heart muscle (EHM), the proposed investigational medicinal product (IMP; designated "Biological Ventricular Assist Tissue" or BioVAT), results in sustainable remuscularization and biological enhancement of myocardial performance in the failing heart. EHM are constructed from defined mixtures of induced pluripotent stem cell (iPSC)-derived cardiomyocytes and stromal cells in a bovine collagen type I hydrogel. Comprehensive preclinical testing confirmed the rationale for the clinical translation of the myocardial remuscularization strategy by EHM implantation. The patient target population for EHM therapy is patients suffering from advanced heart failure with reduced ejection fraction (HFrEF; EF: ≤35%) and no realistic option for heart transplantation (NCT04396899).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:BioVAT-HF','collection', 90, 1),
