(1307, 'Analyse von zellfreier Tumor DNA bei Patienten mit Plattenepithelkarzinomen des Kopf-Hals Bereichs', '', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:Kopf-Hals-Biobank','collection', 90, 1),
(1308, 'NetBi-omics', 'NetBi-omics ist neben PING und PD-CAN eine der drei von allen 9 Verbünden im "Forschungsnetz Psychische Erkrankungen" (https://fzpe.de/) vom Bundesministerium für Bildung und Forschung konsentierten Querschnittsplattformen.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:NetBi-omics','collection', 90, 1),
(1309, 'Pharma_Krankheitsmodelle', 'Herzmuskelgewebe kann sich nach einem Schaden nicht wieder aufbauen. Sowohl im Erwachsenen- als auch im Kindesalter ist Herzmuskelschwäche eine weitverbreitete Erkrankung, die sich nur schwer behandeln lässt. Im Institut für Pharmakologie und Toxikologie konstruieren wir für die individuelle Herzreparatur bei Herzmuskelschwäche Ersatzherzmuskeln aus Stammzellen und testen sie auf therapeutische Eignung. Unsere Mitarbeiter widmen sich in ihren Untersuchungen auch den Prozessen, die natürlicherweise die Herzentwicklung steuern. Auf diesem Wege gelingt es uns, die Mechanismen von Herzerkrankungen und von therapeutischen Ansätzen der biologischen Herzreparatur besser zu verstehen. Um unerwünschte Arzneimitteleigenschaften bereits vor der ersten klinischen Anwendung besser vorhersagen zu können und damit insgesamt die Arzneimittelsicherheit deutlich zu verbessern, werden in unserem Institut künstliche Gewebesysteme wie zum Beispiel Herzmuskeln, Skelettmuskeln, neuronale Netzwerke und Lebergewebe entwickelt und eingesetzt.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:Pharma_Krankheitsmodelle','collection', 90, 1),
(1310, 'Inhibition of Rho Kinase (ROCK) With Fasudil as Disease-modifying Treatment for Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS)', 'Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) is a progressive neurodegenerative disorder and therapeutic options are limited. The rho kinase (ROCK) inhibitor Fasudil was shown to be neuroprotective, induced axonal regeneration and improved survival and behavioral outcome in models of ALS and other neurodegenerative diseases. The aim of this phase IIa, multi-center and double-blind study is to analyze the safety, tolerability and efficacy of fasudil in two different doses compared to placebo in approximately 16 trial sites in Germany, France and Switzerland. Intravenous application of fasudil will be performed in 80 patients and placebo in 40 patients two times daily for 20 treatment days. The hypothesis is that fasudil is safe and well-tolerated and its application will significantly improve the clinical outcome in patients with ALS (NCT03792490).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:ROCK-ALS','collection', 90, 1),
(1311, 'Effect of Anti-Fibrotic Therapy on Regression of Myocardial Fibrosis after Transcatheter Aortic Valve Implantation (TAVI) in Aortic Stenosis Patients with High Fibrotic Burden', 'The narrowing of the aortic valve (aortic valve stenosis) sometimes leads to a very pronounced pathological increase in the connective tissue of the heart muscle, a kind of scarring. This scarring is medically referred to as fibrosis. Severe cardiac fibrosis has a negative impact on heart recovery and long-term survival after surgery to replace a heart valve. The aim of this study is to investigate the effects of anti-fibrotic drugs (spironolactone and/or dihydralazine) on the increase in connective tissue in the heart muscle and the long-term survival of the patient after surgery to replace a heart valve (DRKS00019893).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:Reduce-MFA','collection', 90, 1),
(1312, 'Molekular- und zellbiologische Analysen zur Erforschung und Verbesserung der Therapie des Rektumkarzinoms (KFO 179)', 'The aim of the investigations is to use blood and tumour samples to gain a better understanding of the basics of carcinogenesis and to predict the response of tumours to established therapeutic concepts. This should enable an optimized treatment concept tailored to the patient ("therapy stratification"). In addition, the samples will be used to expand therapeutic options by developing new substances.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:Rektumkarzinom','collection', 90, 1),
(1313, 'Efficacy of Team-Based Care for Distressed Patients in Secondary Prevention of Chronic Coronary Heart Disease', 'To confirm the efficacy of a team-based, multidisciplinary intervention addressing both medical and psychosocial risk factors delivered via a blended collaborative care strategy (TeamCare; TC). This strategy adds a trained care manager (CM) who is supervised by an interdisciplinary specialist team consisting of specialists in mental health and internal medicine/cardiology to usual care. The CM interacts closely with the patients and their treating physicians who stay in charge of all medical decisions. We intend to close the gap in comprehensive long-term follow-up care for patients suffering from both chronic coronary heart disease (CHD) and psychosocial distress by improving their health behaviors and health-related quality of life (HRQoL), which in turn can reduce risk factor burden, morbidity and mortality. Our primary hypothesis is that TC for both CHD and psychosocial distress will improve patients’ HRQoL significantly more than usual care for these conditions through improved risk factor control and reduced psychosocial distress. Secondary hypotheses are that TC will improve health behaviors, treatment adherence, cardiac risk factors, psychosocial functioning, mood and anxiety symptoms, and health care utilization in a sustainable way and beyond the end of the intervention (DRKS00020824).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:TEACH','collection', 90, 1),
(1314, 'Translational Registry for Cardiomyopathies', '', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:TORCH','collection', 90, 1),
(1315, 'Translational Registry for Cardiomyopathies-Plus (Second Phase)', 'The DZHK TranslatiOnal Registry for CardiomyopatHies (DZHK TORCH) represents a unique resource of clinical data and high quality biological samples to enable innovative clinical and molecular studies on cardiomyopathies (CMP). This register is now to be expanded with a second phase (DZHK TORCH-Plus). The second phase DZHK TORCH-Plus consists of 4 main modules: 1. "Clinical phenotyping, follow-up & biosampling" 2. "Genomics", 3. "Inflammation" and 4. "Biomarker". The central aims are 1) to significantly increase the number of probands (n = 4340) in order to better address the different types of CMPs, especially patients with rare CMP forms such as LVNC and ARVC or with probably molecularly explainable cardiomyopathies (familial DCM), 2) to prolong the longitudinal with a further follow-up to achieve sufficient events and thereby derive clinical recommendations for risk assessment, 3) to increase the number of probands with state-of-the-art phenotyping, 4) to pinpoint the effect of myocardial inflammation, fibrosis, gender and to determine or predict genotypes based for outcome, 5) to validate novel biomarkers developed in other DZHK studies, and 6) to foster active cooperation with international CMP registries and partners from industry (NCT04265040).', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:TORCH-Plus','collection', 90, 1),
(1316, 'UMGöttingen Collection', 'The Biobank provides access to quality-assured samples and data from UMG''s own collection of biospecimens, defined and implemented in cooperation with experts from the fields of oncology, neuroscience and cardiovascular medicine.', 'bbmri-eric:ID:DE_UMGB:collection:UMG-Sammlung','collection', 90, 1),
